Colonel Sean Conley, personal physician to United States President, Donald Trump, has said that he experienced two episodes of blood-oxygen drops and was administered a steroid, Dexamethasone, as well as oxygen as part of his treatment. Trump and his wife, Melania, tested positive for COVID-19 on Friday.  He has since been admitted at the Walter Reed Military Medical Center in Wahington DC. See Also






